description:
File: lichen/subsys/lichen/transport/slip_transport.c
Lines: 591-596, 627-638

slip_transport_is_ready() returns false if uart_dev is NULL:

    bool slip_transport_is_ready(void)
    {
        struct slip_transport_ctx *ctx = &s_ctx;
        return ctx->initialized && ctx->uart_dev != NULL;
    }

However, slip_transport_init() succeeds (returns 0) even when no UART device is available (lines 635-638):

    } else {
        LOG_WRN("SLIP transport: no UART device available");
        ctx->uart_dev = NULL;
    }
    ...
    ctx->initialized = true;
    return 0;  // Success!

This creates an inconsistency: init succeeds, but is_ready returns false. Callers might:
1. Call init(), see success (0)
2. Call is_ready(), see false
3. Be confused about the transport state

Fix: Either fail init when no UART device is available, or have is_ready() return true when initialized (even without UART), or document this behavior.
